{
  "local_port": 39888,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you deposit cash at an ATM?",
  "response": "Depositing cash at an ATM is a convenient way to add funds to your bank account without visiting a branch. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you through the process:\n\n### 1. **Find a Compatible ATM**\n- **Bank's ATM:** It's often easiest to use an ATM operated by your own bank to avoid potential fees and ensure full functionality.\n- **Nearby Locations:** If you don't have an ATM nearby from your bank, look for reputable networks (like Visa, Mastercard, or shared branch networks) to find alternative options.\n\n### 2. **Prepare Your Cash**\n- **Organize Bills:** Ensure all bills are unfolded, not crinkled or torn.\n- **Check for Accents:** Remove any paper clips, staples, or anything that might interfere with the deposit process.\n\n### 3. **Insert Your Debit or ATM Card**\n- **Locate the Card Slot:** Typically found on the front of the machine.\n- **Insert Correctly:** Insert the card as indicated by the machine's prompts (usually with the chip facing up or a specific direction).\n\n### 4. **Enter Your Personal Identification Number (PIN)**\n- **Secure Entry:** Use the keypad to enter your PIN securely.\n- **Privacy:** Shield the keypad with your hand to prevent others from seeing your PIN.\n\n### 5. **Select the Deposit Option**\n- **Main Menu:** Once logged in, navigate the on-screen menu.\n- **Choose Account:** Select the type of account you want to deposit into (e.g., checking, savings).\n\n### 6. **Choose Cash Deposit**\n- **Select Cash:** Some ATMs offer both cash and check deposit options; choose cash.\n- **Envelope vs. Envelope-Free:**\n  - **Envelope ATM:** If your ATM requires an envelope, the machine will provide one. Insert your cash and any required deposit slip into the envelope before placing it in the designated slot.\n  - **Envelope-Free ATM:** Modern ATMs may accept cash directly without an envelope. Simply place the cash into the provided slot when prompted.\n\n### 7. **Insert Your Cash**\n- **Follow Instructions:** The ATM may guide you to insert bills one at a time or all at once, depending on the machine\u2019s capabilities.\n- **Confirm Amounts:** Some ATMs will count the bills and display the total amount detected.\n\n### 8. **Review and Confirm the Deposit**\n- **Verify Details:** Ensure the deposit amount and account selection are correct.\n- **Confirm:** Approve the transaction to proceed.\n\n### 9. **Finalize the Transaction**\n- **Wait for Confirmation:** The ATM will process the deposit and may provide a receipt.\n- **Choose Receipt Options:** Decide if you want a printed receipt, an email, or no receipt.\n\n### 10. **Retrieve Your Card and Receipt**\n- **Take Your Card:** Ensure you don't leave your card behind.\n- **Collect Your Receipt:** If you opted for one, take your receipt and keep it for your records.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n- **Check Deposit Limits:** Some ATMs have daily deposit limits or restrictions on the number of bills.\n- **Keep Records:** Always keep your receipt until you confirm the deposit has been credited to your account.\n- **Stay Secure:** Be aware of your surroundings to protect your personal information and cash.\n- **Understand Fees:** Using an out-of-network ATM might incur fees. Check with your bank regarding ATM usage policies.\n\nBy following these steps, you can efficiently deposit cash into your bank account using an ATM. If you encounter any issues, don't hesitate to contact your bank's customer service for assistance.",
